{
  "id": "indus_phase33_t1_sa_syllable",
  "name": "Indus Phase-33 T1 — SA Decipherment M77 → Dravidian Syllable LM (Fixed)",
  "description": "Phase-33 T1: The CORRECTED Phase-32 T4 run. Two bugs fixed: (1) DravidianSyllableLM now properly populates bigram_freq and ranked so BigramScorer works; (2) IndusAnchorSetSyllable maps INDUS_FINAL_ANCHORS to syllable tokens (not whole Tamil words) compatible with the syllable LM. Expected: SA should now converge meaningfully and produce syllable-level assignments (ka, ta, na, mi, etc.) rather than random word-level Tamil assignments. If mean_consistency > 0.5 and hci_count > 30, the syllable-level model is discriminative and supports the Dravidian hypothesis. Compare to Sanskrit T7 redo for falsification. Citations: E.1 (DEDR), A.12 (Mahadevan 2003 TB), A.1 (M77), C.2 (Parpola 2010).",
